            <h3 id="touch-target-size" class="doc-h3">Touch Target Size</h3>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Mobile and tablet platforms require specific tap areas to prevent accidental clicks.</p>
            <div style="margin-top: 16px; padding: 24px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-radius: 12px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 24px;">
              <div style="width: 44px; height: 44px; background: rgba(37,99,235,0.1); border: 1px dashed var(--prism-violet); border-radius: 8px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; color: var(--prism-violet); font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; flex-shrink: 0;">44px</div>
              <div>
                <div style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 15px; color: var(--prism-text);">Minimum Target: 44&#215;44px</div>
                <div style="font-size: 14px; color: var(--prism-text-muted); margin-top: 4px;">Breadcrumb links should have at least 44px touch target height on mobile. Use transparent padding if the text height is smaller than the minimum target.</div>
              </div>
